2.00	Grande_Ludovisi_sarcophagus	Grande Ludovisi sarcophagus	The Grande Ludovisi sarcophagus is a 3rd century, 1.53m high ancient Roman sarcophagus displayed at the palazzo Altemps in Rome. It came from a tomb near the Porta Tiburtina, discovered in 1621. The lid showed submitting barbarians and a bust of a female figure but is now lost, destroyed whilst on display in Mainz in 1945.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Grande_Ludovisi_Altemps_Inv8574.jpg/350px-Grande_Ludovisi_Altemps_Inv8574.jpg
